                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-defend2536" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18230910-290-off1555" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-off1555" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-off1555" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18230910-290-cd1556" type="crimeDate">6th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-290-off1555 t18230910-290-cd1556"></join>, a half-crown, the money of 
                     <persName id="t18230910-290-victim2537" type="victimName">
                        John 
                        Brown
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-victim2537" type="surname" value="Brown"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18230910-290-victim2537" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18230910-290-victim2537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-290-off1555 t18230910-290-victim2537"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , his master
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN BROWN. I am a <rs id="t18230910-290-viclabel1557" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-290-victim2537 t18230910-290-viclabel1557"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18230910-290-crimeloc1558">Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-290-crimeloc1558" type="placeName" value="Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-290-crimeloc1558" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-290-off1555 t18230910-290-crimeloc1558"></join>; the prisoner was in my service about three months. On the 6th of August, a cutler marked all the money in the tills on the head side, opposite to the face. About eleven o'clock at night, I gave 17 s. to a witness to put in the till, having myself first counted it; there were five half-crowns among it. The shutters were then shut, but the drawers not closed - no more customers came. It was his duty to empty the till at night - he did not know that I had done it. He came and separated the halfpence from the silver as usual - and in three or four minutes I came from outside the door with the witness, and immediately counted the silver, and found a half-crown missing. I accused him of taking it - he denied it. I found it in his pocket with other silver, and after some time he acknowledged taking it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PRENDERGAST. Q. Did you know what the till contained - A. I might have left 1 s. in it, among the copper. I found only four half-crowns left. I said if his friends came forward, I would let him go. I wanted to know how much he had taken, as he acknowledged he had been robbing me ever since he came. I bought his friends might persuade him to tell me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-290-person2538">
                  THOMAS 
                  HART
               <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2538" type="surname" value="HART"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2538" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2538" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was fellow <rs id="t18230910-290-deflabel1559" type="occupation">shopman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-290-defend2536 t18230910-290-deflabel1559"></join> with the prisoner. Between ten and eleven o'clock, Mr. Brown gave me some money, which he said was marked - I put it into the till, when the silver was taken out at night; the prisoner was not in the shop at the time. The 17 s. consisted of half-crowns, and other coin. The shop was shut, and no customer came afterwards. The prisoner came in about five minutes after, and in three or four minutes the half-crown was missed. My master searched him, and found it on him among other money.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did your master say he would let him go if his friends came forward - A. He said, if he would say where his friends were, he would send for them. I saw no violence used to him. I saw him laying on his back, he was handcuffed before the officer came.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-290-person2539">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SPOONER
               <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2539" type="surname" value="SPOONER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2539" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2539" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable, and was sent for, and found him handcuffed - the money was delivered to me.</p>
               <p>JOHN BROWN. Here is the half-crown, it is marked P. H.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-290-person2540">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CATTEN
               <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2540" type="surname" value="CATTEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2540" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-person2540" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a cutler. I marked this halfcrown for Brown.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. You were present when this charge was made - A. Yes; Brown said, if he had friends, he would write to them - he said he had none.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18230910-290-verdict1560" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18230910-290-verdict1560" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
